Key Match Events: Kevin Durant led the team in scoring with 25 points, while Bradley Beal and Devin Booker had 24 and 15 points respectively.
The Suns captured a 116-113 win in overtime.
James Harden led the Clippers with 29 points and 12 rebounds.
Ivica Zubac had 21 points and nine rebounds.
Pre-Game Insights: The Suns, anchored by their star trio of Durant, Devin Booker, and Bradley Beal, have a fresh start with new head coach Mike Budenholzer.
The Clippers lost Paul George during the offseason and are grappling with the indefinite absence of star forward Kawhi Leonard due to ongoing knee issues.
